The paper focuses on requirements engineering and quality assurance, which are both subfields of software engineering (cs.SE). The concept of "code smells" is borrowed from software development, which suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The use of a prototype called "Smella" implies a focus on software tools and systems (cs.SI). The evaluation of the approach in practical environments suggests a connection to cybernetics and systems (cs.CY). Finally, the use of machine learning for smell detection suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
